news.title: Indore: Development work of Multi Modal logistic park to begin by end of 2024
news.para: MMLP is being established in a PPP (DBFOT) mode across 112.6 hectares near Pithampur in Dhar district, encompassing 90 hectare of private land from four villages and 22 hectares of government land.

news.title: China's Beijing, Shanghai announce tax breaks to boost property markets
news.para: Other major Chinese cities are widely expected to follow suit and the measures come on the heels of some tax breaks on home and land transactions unveiled by China's finance ministry last week.

news.title: Indore civic body demolishes illegal portions of 63 houses for road widening
news.para: Senior IMC officials said notices informing residents about the impending demolition of unauthorized extensions to their property were issued a week ago. As several residents failed to comply with the notice, the civic body decided to launch the demolition drive on Monday.

news.title: Karnataka govt faces Rs 76 crore legal notice from Adani Group over unsold Malaysian sand
news.para: The Krishnapatnam Port Company (KPCL), owned by Adani Group, has issued legal notices, demanding compensation of Rs 76 crore towards uncleared stocks worth Rs 10 crore.

news.title: Bhopal: FIR registered against two landlords for failing tenant verification
news.para: ​​The landlords, identified as Harisingh Yadav and Manoj Kumar Gupta, both residents of N-Sector in Ayodhya Nagar, were found in breach of the directive during routine patrolling and checks.

news.title: Housing minister lauds states and UTs for role in successful implementation of PMAY
news.para: In a statement, the housing and urban affairs ministry said that the minister highlighted the PMAY-U 2.0 Scheme, its impact on the economy and allied sectors, creation of more than three crore estimated employment opportunities for people.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government's new order raises electrical safety concerns for highrises
news.para: The new rules state that only those high-rise buildings with a voltage level above 650V should be inspected by the electrical inspectorate. Buildings with a voltage level between 250V and 650V can be self-certified by the builders through chartered electrical safety engineers (CESE).

news.title: ArisInfra Solutions receives Sebi's approval to raise Rs 600 crore via IPO
news.para: As per the draft papers, the Mumbai-based company plans to utilise proceeds of the issue for funding the working-capital requirements of the company, investment in subsidiary, Buildmex-Infra, repayment of loan and for general corporate purposes.

news.title: Over 4.5 lakh defaulters owe Rs 1,881 crore property tax to Gurugram civic body
news.para: According to the corporation data, 100 major defaulters owe the corporation Rs 288.4 crore. The remaining Rs 1593 crore is owed by 4.9 lakh property owners.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt signs MoA with housing ministry to launch PMAY-U 2.0
news.para: The two sides will roll out the second phase of Prime Minister Awas Scheme (urban) (PMAY-U 2.0) signing the document was essential between

news.title: Country Garden submits offshore debt restructuring plan to creditors: Sources
news.para: The company revised its cash flow projection in the proposal, said two sources who have direct knowledge of the plan and another person familiar with the matter. The projection is a standard part of a debt revamp process to show a firm's ability to repay.

news.title: hBits lease out 37,362 sq ft office space in Thane
news.para: The grade A commercial asset, valued at Rs 54.66 crore, is situated in Ashar IT Park at Wagle Estate. The valuation is based on the rental rate as per the signed agreement with the tenant.

news.title: WeWork India appoints Jitendra Mohandas Virwani as non-executive chairman
news.para: Adnan Ahmad, member of the board of directors of WeWork Inc. and senior advisor to Yardi Systems, Inc., will also join the WeWork India's board of directors, taking over from David Mayland, vice president, head of corporate development, WeWork Inc.

news.title: China's revenue from government land sales down 22.9% year on year in Jan-Oct 2024
news.para: China's local governments have long relied on land sales to boost their revenues, but this source of income has sharply declined since 2022 as cash-strapped developers have reduced their land acquisitions.

news.title: Four listed REITs distributes Rs 2,754 crore to unitholders in H1 FY25: IRA
news.para: These four publicly listed real estate investment trusts (REITs) in India are Brookfield India Real Estate Trust, Embassy Office Parks REIT, Mindspace Business Parks REIT, and Nexus Select Trust.

news.title: Hubballi residents still waiting to get E-Aasthi certificates
news.para: HDMC is making citizens run from pillar to post for 8-9 months to obtain a certificate. Personnel handling the process are allegedly demanding bribes to issue E-Aasthi certificates. Many a times, they say the applicant's file is lost and insist they re-submit it.

news.title: Cost of construction rises up to 11% annually in 2024 across real estate segments: Colliers
news.para: The cumulative effect of rise in the prices of four key construction materials including cement, steel, copper and aluminum have been relatively low.

news.title: Telangana government sanctions Rs 205 crore for Warangal airport after GMR issues NOC
news.para: According to the GO issued on Sunday, the Airports Authority of India (AAI) in July 2022, informed the state government that it is ready to develop Warangal Airport for A-320 type of aircraft for IFR (instrument flight rules) operations and is ready to bear the infrastructure cost, operational and maintenance of the proposed airport.
